France has seized a yacht linked to Rosneft boss Igor Sechin in the Mediterranean port of La Ciotat, the country’s finance minister has said. In a statement Thursday, French finance minister Bruno Le Maire said the vessel was seized overnight as it was being prepared to depart the dock, despite being in need of repairs.   Ukraine: Putin, Macron share ‘not-so-friendly’…     U.S. continues efforts to get India to condemn Russia on…     When U.S forces will attack Russia, by Joe Biden   Read Also: Ukraine: Putin, Macron share ‘not-so-friendly’ phone call The yacht was owned by a company of which Sechin was identified as being the main shareholder, the statement said. Sechin had been included on a list of Russian oligarchs to be subject to European Union sanctions in response to Russia’s invasion of Ukraine. Nbcnews